TipsHeading{<8}Content
89	Alternatively the snitch can be a small yellow ball
90	( tennis balls work great )
91	that is hidden
92	before the game starts
93	by a bystander or referee .
SnitchAsBall{=9}MoreTips
94	Establish boundaries
95	and have the seekers look for the snitch .
SeekersLookForSnitch{<11}BeatersTips
96	Beaters can try hitting the bludgers around in the air with a shortened hockey sticks or a short bat .
97	They could also use regular-length hockey sticks
98	to hit bludgers
99	( perhaps wiffle balls )
100	on the ground .
BeatersItemsOptions{<13}EasySuggestion
101	The simplest way is to just peg players
102	by throwing dodge balls .
BeatersTips{>12}BroomsOptional
103	It may be easier to play without brooms
104	( but also less fun ! ) .
BeatersTips{=10}Snitch
105	Remember that the snitch runner ,
106	if you choose to use one ,
107	is not an actual player in the game ,
108	therefore , not bound by any of the rules .
SnitchNotBoundByRules{>11}SnitchFreeToDoWhatever
109	If desired ,
110	the snitch is able to do whatever he or she wants
111	to avoid capture .
112	See How to Be a Snitch in Quidditch for more information .
Play{>6}Variations
113	You can play water quidditch in a pool .
114	Almost all the same rules apply .
115	Have someone throw something
116	( the snitch )
117	on a line into the pool at regular intervals .
QuidditchPool{=8}ChangingProps
118	They can even use fake snitches .
119	You can buy authentic looking brooms
120	to make the game more realistic .
QuidditchInPool{<7}MoreVariations
121	There is a very large Quidditch community ,
122	have a look at the IQA website
123	to find teams near you .
IQAWebsiteCommunity{<9}Variation
124	One variation is Quarter Snitch Quidditch .
125	Find a quarter or another small coin .
126	Have both of the teams turn around
127	and have the referee throw it into the grass or pitch
128	while the teams are n't looking .
UseQuarterForSnitch{>10}SeekersLookForQuarter
129	Play
130	while the seekers look for the snitch .
FirstVariation{=8}AnotherVariation
131	Another variation is where the referee places the snitch somewhere in the field
132	( in this case it 's a small ball ) .
133	The seeker has to find the snitch blindfolded ,
134	relying only on the coach 's instructions ,
135	while the game is still on .
